  <img class="bigimage" src="/content/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/m_home.jpg" />  
  <h5>Metaversum</h5>
<p>Welcome to Metaversum.<br />
For a brief introduction to the company, its management team and current vacancies, <a href="http://www.metaversum.com/content/company/">click here</a>.</p>
<hr /><!-- Twinity    ==================================== --></p>
<h5>Twinity. Powered by real life.</h5>
<p class="img_right"><a title="Twinity" href="/content/products/"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-31" title="twinity" src="/content/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/logo_beta.gif" alt="Twinity logo" width="212" height="76" /></a></p>
<h2>Introducing Twinity</h2>
<p>Metaversum’s <a title="Go to twinity.com" href="http://www.twinity.com/" target="_blank">Twinity</a> is the world’s first mirror world made of real people and real places. The virtual cities of Berlin, Singapore and London have already launched in Twinity, with other international cities set to join them soon. Twinity is currently in public Beta and open for business. <a href="/content/products/">Tell me more about Twinity</a>.</p>
<hr /><!-- Award    ==================================== --></p>
<h5 class="anchor">Award</h5>
<p class="img_right"><a href="http://www.metaversum.com/content/metaversum-and-twinity-has-been-elected-a-red-herring-100-europe-winner-2009/"><img style="border: 0px initial initial;" title="Red Herring" src="/content/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/redherring.jpg" alt="Red Herring" /></a></p>
<h2>Red Herring Europe Winner</h2>
<p><strong>Metaversum has been elected a Red Herring 100 Europe Winner for its 3D online world Twinity.</strong></p>
<p class="p_left">&#8220;We feel honored to receive the Red Herring 100 Europe award. This clearly confirms our vision of a 3D world based on real cities, allowing real people to interact and communicate with each other.” says Metaversum CEO Jochen Hummel. <a href="http://www.metaversum.com/content/metaversum-and-twinity-has-been-elected-a-red-herring-100-europe-winner-2009/">Click here for more info.</a></p>
    
